      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example featuring the legendary S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, delivering linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. It comes equipped with a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and the factory M-Variable differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis has been proactively maintained with rear subframe reinforcement and refreshed VANOS seals to ensure mechanical longevity. Riding on a staggered set of Style 67 wheels, the suspension maintains its original geometry with upgraded polyurethane bushings for sharpened turn-in response. Cosmetically honest with a strong service history, this E46 represents a balanced mix of analog feel and precision engineering.",
